label.value: Positive CSF Toxoplasma gondii antibody positivity

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of Toxoplasma gondii.

A positive result of the tuberculin skin test suggesting previous expouse or infection with mycobacterium teberculosis. A standard dose of five tuberculin units (TU) (0.1ml) is injected intradermally (into the skin) and read 48 to 72 h later. A person who has been exposed to the bacteria is expected to mount an immune response in the skin containing the bacterial proteins. The volar aspect of the forearm is the preferred site of test. The basis of reading is the presence or absence of induration, which may be determined by inspection (from a side view against the light as well as by direct light) and by palpation. For standardization, the diameter of induration should be measured transversely to the long axis of the forearm and recorded in millimeters.
The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Treponema pallidum.

label.value: Positive CSF Borrelia burgdorferi antibody positivity

definition.value: The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of Borrelia burgdorferi.
The presence of antibodies in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) that react against a component of JC-virus (also known as JC-polyomavirus and John Cunningham virus).
The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of the proximal tibia.
Growth of bacteria in a culture dervied from ascites fluid.
A small (less than 5 mm in diameter), elevated, circumscribed, solid, palpable mass located in thte mucosa of the oral cavity.
A palpable swelling in the scalp caused by an increase in interstitial fluid volume (excess fluid).

label.value: Positive brain-tissue rabies nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of rabies nucleic acid in brain tissue by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label.value: Positive respiratory tract Bordetella pertussis nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of Bordetella pertussis PCR nucleic acid in in nasopharyngeal secretions by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

label.value: Demonstration of acid-fast bacilli in wound tissue
Positive tissue encapsulated budding yeast test

definition.value: Identification of encapsulated budding yeasts in smears of body fluids, secretions, exudates, or other specimens.
Growth of coccidioidomycosis in a culture derived from skin or an organ.
Concentration of transcobalamin I in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Diminished sulfotransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts

definition.value: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.50) outside of the limits of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts. It is also known as alpha-acetylglucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminidase, N-acetyl-alpha-glucosaminidase, and alpha-D-2-acetamido-2-deoxyglucosidase.
The concentration of trihydroxycholestanoic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of glyoxylic acid in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates of stainable substances within hepatocytes.
Presence of abnormal vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles) in the sarcolemma. The vacuoles are often associated with cytoplasmic and occasionally intranuclear eosinophilic inclusions.
